title: 3 European Dividend Stocks Yielding Up To 6.5%
description: As European markets experience a positive shift, with the STOXX Europe 600 Index rising 1.40% amid hopes of lower U.S. borrowing costs, investors are increasingly eyeing dividend stocks for their potential to provide steady income streams in uncertain economic times. In this environment, selecting dividend stocks that offer reliable yields and robust fundamentals can be an effective strategy for those looking to capitalize on market stability and growth opportunities.
content:
As European markets experience a positive shift, with the STOXX Europe 600 Index rising 1.40% amid hopes of lower U.S. borrowing costs, investors are increasingly eyeing dividend stocks for their potential to provide steady income streams in uncertain economic times. In this environment, selecting dividend stocks that offer reliable yields and robust fundamentals can be an effective strategy for those looking to capitalize on market stability and growth opportunities.

Click here to see the full list of 214 stocks from our Top European Dividend Stocks screener.

We'll examine a selection from our screener results.

Overview: What's Cooking Group NV, along with its subsidiaries, produces and sells meat products and ready meals, with a market cap of €224.60 million.

Operations: The company's revenue segment for ready meals amounts to €403.55 million.

What's Cooking Group has demonstrated a reliable dividend history over the past decade, with recent increases reflecting its commitment to shareholders. However, its current dividend yield of 3.72% is below the top tier in Belgium. The company's dividends are not well covered by earnings due to a high payout ratio of 90.1%, though they are supported by cash flows with a low cash payout ratio of 24.5%. Recent announcements include an annual dividend increase and special cash dividends scheduled for July 2025 payments.
• Get an in-depth perspective on What's Cooking Group's performance by reading our dividend report here.
• Insights from our recent valuation report point to the potential undervaluation of What's Cooking Group shares in the market.

Overview: Ålandsbanken Abp operates as a commercial bank serving private individuals and companies in Finland and Sweden, with a market cap of €640.51 million.

Operations: Ålandsbanken Abp generates its revenue from several segments including IT (€54.13 million), Premium Banking (€68.99 million), Corporate and Other (€18.16 million), and Private Banking, which includes Asset Management (€47.40 million).
summary: As European markets continue to improve, investors are increasingly looking for dividend stocks that offer steady income streams in uncertain economic times. What's Cooking Group NV produces and sells meat products and ready meals, with a market cap of €224.60 million and a revenue segment for ready meals totalling €403.55 million. However, its current dividend yield of 3.72% is below the top tier in Belgium and its high payout ratio of 90.1%. The company's recent announcements include an annual dividend increase and special cash dividends scheduled for July 2025.
shortSummary: As European markets experience a positive shift, dividend stocks like What's Cooking Group and Ålandsbanken Abp offer reliable yields and robust financial fundamentals.

Ålandsbanken Abp, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a commercial bank for private individuals and companies in Finland and Sweden. It offers net interest income from all deposit accounts, including savings accounts, time deposits and cash accounts connected to securities accounts, net commission income from deposits, cashier and payment intermediate services, debit and credit card, the Premium concept, bank safety deposit boxes, etc.; and income from exchanging currencies. The company also provides financial services, such as net interest income from all lending products and securities account loans, as well as lending commissions and guarantee commissions.
